				<li>Folio was redesigned by Daniel Gullo, Columba Stewart, William Straub and Chad Lavigne of sdg in 2016 as part of the development and launch of vHMML 2.0</li>
				<li>vHMML 3.0 was developed by Bryan Lor and Chad LaVigne of sdg</li>
			</ul>
			<h3 id="TECHNICAL" class="subheading jumptarget">Technical</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><span class="redtext italicstext">v</span>HMML 
					is written in Java&#8482; and HTML running
					on an <a href="https://tomcat.apache.org/" target="_blank">Apache
						Tomcat</a> server
				<li><span class="redtext italicstext">v</span>HMML uses <a href="https://www.mysql.com/"
					target="_blank">MySQL</a> as its database</li>
				<li>Image viewing in Reading Room and Folio uses the <a href="http://projectmirador.org/"
					target="_blank">Mirador</a> <a href="http://iiif.io/" target="_blank">IIIF</a> viewer</li>
